It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a little decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and the hearth. Cover the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand it. Build a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a quick sketch in pencil...
The messy stage is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the chimney; all dried up :(
Ready for the plastering next week
Pleased with the little niche on the side
Insert the new wardrobe here (it's not like we've already started drawing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought about adding a lovely little vent to prevent the chimney from getting damp
The chimney sweep took care of installing the cap and the damper. That should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plastering is done. We'll install the floor tomorrow !
The cork underlayment is laid, I improvised a wood shavings extractor with a toilet paper roll as an accessory for the vacuum 😂
Part of the boards are sorted and ready to be laid. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress has been slow today because of extremely delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition into the hallway (which is also being laid). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but on wobbly legs! Cherry on top: the unworkable instructions for assembling the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
Still to do: the hallway floor and all the baseboards. The decorator comes in a month, so in the meantime, at home, it's chic plaster without any fuss
Evening DIY session to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw or a chisel where we want the floor to be perfectly fitted.
The cork underlayment for the hallway is also laid
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then off at 5am this morning to pick up Chose 1 from Heathrow, then a nap and the final stretch for the hallway; baseboards installed. We'll take care of the sealing once the glue has dried.
